Chapter Two

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 天 下 皆 知 美 之 為 美 斯 惡 已  | In the world, when all know that  |
| •                                 | the action of beauty is           |
|                                   |                                   |
| 皆 知 善 之 為 善 斯 不 善 已 •   |       beautiful, then ugliness    |
|                                   | ensues.                           |
| (•)故 有 無 相 生 •               |                                   |
|                                   | When all know that the action of  |
| 難 易 相 成 •                     | good is goodness, then            |
|                                   |                                   |
| 長 短 相 較 •                     |       not-good ensues.            |
|                                   |                                   |
| 高 下 相 傾 •                     |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 音 聲 相 和 •                     |                                   |
|                                   | Therefore : being and non-being   |
| 前 後 相 隨 •                     | create each other,                |
|                                   |                                   |
| 是 以 聖 人                       | Difficult and easy complete each  |
|                                   | other,                            |
| 處 無 為 之 事                    |                                   |
|                                   | Long and short contrast each      |
| 行 不 言 之 教                    | other,                            |
|                                   |                                   |
| 萬 物 作 __ 而 不 (始) •          | High and low lean on each other,  |
|                                   |                                   |
| 生 而 不 有                       | Tone and voice harmonize each     |
|                                   | other,                            |
| 為 而 不 恃 •                     |                                   |
|                                   | Before and after follow each      |
| 功 成 而 弗 居 •                  | other.                            |
|                                   |                                   |
| (•)夫 唯 弗 居 •                  |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 是 以 不 去 •                     | Thus the sage :                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Lives by using non-action in his  |
|                                   | duties,                           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | And practicing no-talking in his  |
|                                   | teachings.                        |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | The ten thousand creatures arise, |
|                                   | but do not have a                 |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       beginning.                  |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Creating but not possessing;      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Acting, but not concerned with    |
|                                   | the results;                      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Accomplishing tasks, but not      |
|                                   | dwelling on them.                 |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Now : only because there is no    |
|                                   | dwelling,                         |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Thus the results do not depart.   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| In the world², when all know that | Notes                             |
| the action of beauty is           |                                   |
|                                   | A : compare to #40, where         |
