Chapter Three

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 不 尚 賢                          | Not honoring those who are        |
|                                   | esteemable                        |
| 使 民 不 爭                       |                                   |
|                                   | Ensures that the citizens do not  |
| 不 貴 難 得 之 貨                 | strive.                           |
|                                   |                                   |
| 使 民 不 為 盜                    | Not valuing rare goods            |
|                                   |                                   |
| 不 見 可 欲                       | Ensures that the citizens do not  |
|                                   | act like thieves.                 |
| 使 民 心 不 亂 •                  |                                   |
|                                   | Not showing that which can be     |
| 是 以 聖 人 之 治 •               | desired                           |
|                                   |                                   |
| 虛 其 心 實 其 腹                 | Ensures that the citizens’        |
|                                   | heart/minds do not become         |
| 弱 其 志 強 其 骨                 |                                   |
|                                   |       confused.                   |
| 常 使 民 無 知 無 欲 •            |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 使 夫 智 者 不 敢 為 __ •         |                                   |
|                                   | Thus the governing of the sage    |
| 為 無 為 則 無 不 治 [矣(•)] •    |                                   |
|                                   | Empties their heart/minds, fills  |
|                                   | their stomachs,                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Weakens their ambitions,          |
|                                   | strengthens their bones.          |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | By always ensuring that the       |
|                                   | citizens are                      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       without-knowledge and       |
|                                   | without-desire,                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Those who make men wise will not  |
|                                   | dare to act.                      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Act with non-action, then all     |
|                                   | will be governed!                 |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| Not honoring [those who are]      | Notes                             |
| esteemable                        |                                   |
|                                   | A : presumably of striving,       |
|                                   | greed, and confusion              |
|                                   |                                   |
|  [virtuous,talented]              | B : presumably referring to       |
|                                   | Confucians; earlier sources use   |
| Ensures that the citizens do not  | the non-Confucian term            |
| strive.                           | “knowledgeable” instead of        |
|          [cause,make]             | “wise”                            |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦Not valuing rare² [à] goods      |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| Ensures that the citizens do not  | Cross-references                  |
| act like thieves.                 |                                   |
|                                   | no striving : #8, #22, #66, #68,  |
|                                   | #73, #81                          |
|                                   |                                   |
|          [cause,make]             | rare goods : #12, #64             |
|                                   |                                   |
| Not showing [that which] can be   | without-desire : #1, #34, #37,    |
| desired                           | #57                               |
|                                   |                                   |
| Ensures that the citizens’        | weak : #29, #36, #40, #55, #76,   |
| heart/minds do not become         | #78                               |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | strong : #29, #30, #33, #36, #52, |
| confused.                         | #55, #67, #78                     |
|                                   |                                   |
|          [cause,make]             | not daring to act : #64, #67, #69 |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦Thus² the governing of the sage² | non-action : #2, #37, #38, #43,   |
|                                   | #48, #57, #63, #64                |
| ♦Empties their heart/minds^(A),   |                                   |
| fills° their stomachs,            | act with non-action : #63         |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦Weakens their ambitions,         | anti-Confucian : #18, #19, #27,   |
| strengthens their bones.          | #33, #38                          |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦By always ensuring that the      |                                   |
| citizens are                      |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|             without-knowledge and |                                   |
| without-desire,                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|          [cause,make]             |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| Those who make men wise*^(B) will |                                   |
| not dare to act.                  |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| Act with non-action, then all²    |                                   |
| will be governed !                |                                   |
