Chapter Four

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 道  (盅) 而 用 之 (有) 不 盈 •    | Dao is like a cup or bowl, yet    |
|                                   | use it and there exists no        |
| 淵 兮 似 萬 物 之 宗 •            |                                   |
|                                   |       need to fill it.            |
| 挫 其 銳 •                        |                                   |
|                                   | Profound and deep!, it appears to |
| 解 其 紛 •                        | be the ancestor of the ten        |
|                                   |                                   |
| 和 其 光                          |       thousand creatures.         |
|                                   |                                   |
| 同 其 塵                          |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 湛 兮 似 或 存 •                  | It blunts their sharpness,        |
|                                   |                                   |
| 吾 不 知 誰 之 子 •               | Loosens their tangles,            |
|                                   |                                   |
| 象 帝 之 先 •                     | Softens their brightness,         |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Makes them the same as the dust   |
|                                   | of the world.                     |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Deep and profound!, it seems to   |
|                                   | barely exist.                     |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | I do not know whose child it is – |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Its image came before that of     |
|                                   | god.                              |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| Dao is like a cup or bowl^(A),    | Notes                             |
| yet use it and there exists no    |                                   |
|                                   | A : while the symbol used here    |
|       [need to] fill it.          | only appears in one out of four   |
|                                   | sources, it gives the most        |
| Profound and deep !, it appears   | straightforward translation;      |
| to be the ancestor of the         |                                   |
|                                   | Dao is like a cup in that its     |
|       ten thousand creatures.     | usefulness is in its emptiness    |
|                                   | (see #11 and #25)                 |
| It blunts their                   |                                   |
| sharpness,                        | B : this line could just as       |
|             [dampens,subdues]     | likely be translated as           |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦Loosens their tangles,^(B)       |             Clarifies their       |
|                                   | confusion                         |
| ♦Softens their brightness,^(C)    |                                   |
|                                   | C : compare to #58, where the     |
| ♦Makes them the same as the dust  | sage is bright but does not       |
| of the world ^(D).                | dazzle                            |
|                                   |                                   |
| Deep and profound !, it seems to  | D : according to Waley, “dust” is |
| barely exist.^(E)                 | a metaphor for the “noise and     |
|                                   | fuss of everyday life”            |
|                                   |                                   |
|       [might,maybe,perhaps]       | E : compare to #6, where the      |
|                                   | spirit of the valley also “seems  |
| I do not know whose [à] child it  | to exist”                         |
| is –                              |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦Its image came before that of    |                                   |
| god{emperor}.                     | Cross-references                  |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | use does not exhaust : #5, #35    |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | blunt the sharpness : #56         |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | loosen the tangles : #56          |
|                                   |                                   |
