Chapter Five

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 天 地 不 仁                       | Heaven and earth are not kind –   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 以 萬 物 為 芻 狗 •               | Thus the ten thousand creatures   |
|                                   | become as straw dogs to           |
| 聖 人 不 仁 •                     |                                   |
|                                   |       them.                       |
| 以 百 姓 為 芻 狗                 |                                   |
|                                   | The sage is not kind –            |
| 天 地 之 間                       |                                   |
|                                   | Thus the 100 families become as   |
| 其 猶 橐 籥 乎(•)                 | straw dogs to him.                |
|                                   |                                   |
| 虛 而 不 屈                       |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 動 而 愈 出 •                     | The space between heaven and      |
|                                   | earth,                            |
| 多 言 數 窮                       |                                   |
|                                   | How is it just like a bellows or  |
| 不 如 守 中                       | flute?                            |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | It is empty, yet does not run     |
|                                   | out.                              |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | The more it moves, and the more   |
|                                   | it produces.                      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Too much talking is exceptionally |
|                                   | exhausting,                       |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Which is not as good as           |
|                                   | maintaining what is within.       |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| ♦Heaven and earth are not kind* – | Notes                             |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦Thus the ten thousand creatures  | Only lines 5-8 are in GUO         |
| become as straw dogs^(A) to       |                                   |
|                                   | A : Hall&Ames describe “straw     |
|       them.                       | dogs” as items that were          |
|                                   | carefully created for a           |
| ♦The sage² is not kind* –         | sacrificial ritual, and treated   |
|                                   | with great respect during the     |
| ♦Thus the 100 families become as  | ritual, but afterwards were       |
| straw dogs to him.                | casually tossed away and not      |
|                                   | given another thought             |
| The space between [à] heaven and  |                                   |
| earth,                            | B : this sentence could just as   |
|                                   | likely end with “maintaining your |
| [How] is it just like a bellows   | center”                           |
| or flute ?                        |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦It is empty, yet does not run    |                                   |
| o                                 | Cross-references                  |
| ut.                               |                                   |
|                                   | 100 families : #17, #49           |
|                                   |                                   |
