Chapter Six

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 谷 神 不 死                       | The spirit of the valley does not |
|                                   | die –                             |
| 是 謂 玄 牝                       |                                   |
|                                   | It is called the deep and         |
| 玄 牝 之 門                       | mysterious feminine.              |
|                                   |                                   |
| 是 謂 天 地 (之) 根 •             |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 绵 绵 若 存                       | The gateway of this deep and      |
|                                   | mysterious feminine –             |
| 用 之 不 勤                       |                                   |
|                                   | It is called the source of heaven |
|                                   | and earth.                        |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Unbroken, it seems to exist.      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Using it takes no effort.         |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| ♦The spirit of the valley does    | Notes                             |
| not die^(A) –                     |                                   |
|                                   | A :  the qualities (“spirit”) of  |
| It is called the deep and         | a valley (receptiveness,          |
| mysterious feminine.              | openness, emptiness) never leave  |
|                                   | it                                |
| The gateway of this deep and      |                                   |
| mysterious feminine –             | B : compare to #4, where Dao also |
|                                   | “seems to barely exist”           |
| It is called the source of heaven |                                   |
| and earth.                        |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| Unbroken², it seems to exist.^(B) | Cross-references                  |
|                                   |                                   |
| Using it takes no                 | die/death : #33, #42, #50, #67,   |
| effort.                           | #74, #75, #76, #80                |
| [diligence,hard work]             |                                   |
|                                   | valley : #15, #28, #32, #39, #41, |
