Chapter Thirteen

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 寵 辱 若 驚                       | Favor and disgrace seem alarming. |
|                                   |                                   |
| 貴 大 患 若 身 •                  | High rank brings great suffering  |
|                                   | if you have a self.               |
| 何 謂 寵 辱 若 驚                 |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 寵 為 下 得 之 若 驚              |                                   |
|                                   | What is meant by “favor and       |
| 失 之 若 驚 •                     | disgrace seem alarming”?          |
|                                   |                                   |
| 是 謂 寵 辱 若 驚                 | Favor makes you the inferior, so  |
|                                   | gaining it seems alarming.        |
| 何 謂 貴 大 患 若 身              |                                   |
|                                   | Losing it also seems alarming.    |
| 吾 所 以 有 大 患 者 為 吾 有 身  |                                   |
| •                                 | This is what is meant by “favor   |
|                                   | and disgrace seem                 |
| 及 吾 無 身 吾 有 何 患 (•)       |                                   |
|                                   |       alarming”.                  |
| (•)故 貴 以 身 為 天 下 •         |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 若 可 [以] 寄 天 下 [矣(•)] •     |                                   |
|                                   | What is meant by “high rank       |
| 愛 以 身 為 天 下                 | brings great suffering if you     |
|                                   |                                   |
| 若 可 [以] 託 天 下 [矣(•)] •     |       have a self”?               |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | I am the reason that I have great |
|                                   | suffering, I who act like         |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       I have a self.              |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | When I am without a self, how     |
|                                   | could I have suffering?           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Therefore : he who is high        |
|                                   | ranking and uses his self to      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       serve the world –           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | It seems he can thus be entrusted |
|                                   | with the world!                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | He who is loving and uses his     |
|                                   | self to serve the world –         |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | It seems he can thus be entrusted |
|                                   | with the world!                   |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| ♦Favor and disgrace seem          | Notes                             |
| alarming.                         |                                   |
|                                   | A : Ames&Hall point out that      |
| ♦High rank brings great suffering | “favor” here means something that |
| if you have a self.               | is bestowed upon you by a         |
|                                   | superior at their whim, thus it   |
| What is meant by “favor and       | emphasizes your inferiority to    |
| disgrace seem alarming”?          | them; and since it could be taken |
|                                   | away just as easily, merely       |
| Favor makes you the inferior^(A), | gaining it is cause for “alarm”   |
| so gaining it seems               | (worry, anxiety, etc.)            |
|                                   |                                   |
|       alarming.                   | B : this is written in this       |
|                                   | awkward manner to emphasize that  |
| ♦Losing it [also] seems alarming. | it is the personality or          |
|                                   | sense-of-self that is being       |
| This is what is meant by “favor   | talked about (in the translator’s |
| and disgrace seem                 | opinion – see the Introduction    |
|                                   | and cross-references below)       |
|       alarming”.                  |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| What is meant by “high rank       |                                   |
| brings great suffering if you     | Cross-references                  |
|                                   |                                   |
|       have a self”?               | self : #7, #9, #16, #26, #44,     |
|                                   | #52, #54, #66                     |
