Chapter Twenty Three

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 希 言 自 然                       | Minimal words are naturally so.   |
|                                   |                                   |
| (•)故 飄 風 不 終 朝              | Therefore : strong winds do not   |
|                                   | last the entire morning,          |
| 驟 雨 不 終 日•                   |                                   |
|                                   | Sudden rains do not last the      |
| 孰 為 此 者 天 地 •               | entire day.                       |
|                                   |                                   |
| 天 地 尚 不 能 久                 |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 而 況 於 人 乎(•)                 | Who makes these things?  Heaven   |
|                                   | and earth.                        |
| (•)故 從 事 於 道 者              |                                   |
|                                   | Even heaven and earth can not     |
| 道 者 同 於 道                    | maintain them forever,            |
|                                   |                                   |
| 德 者 同 於 德                    | And so how much less can people?  |
|                                   |                                   |
| 失 者 同 於 失 •                  |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 同 於 道 者                       | Therefore : of those who engage   |
|                                   | in Dao –                          |
| 道 亦 樂 得 之                    |                                   |
|                                   | He who Daos is one with Dao.      |
| 同 於 德 者                       |                                   |
|                                   | He who Des is one with De.        |
| 德 亦 樂 得 之                    |                                   |
|                                   | He who loses is one with the      |
| 同 於 失 者                       | loss.                             |
|                                   |                                   |
| 失 亦 樂 得 之                    |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 信 不 足 焉 有 不 信 __           | For he who is one with Dao,       |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Dao is also pleased to have       |
|                                   | him.                              |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | For he who is one with De,        |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | De is also pleased to have        |
|                                   | him.                              |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | For he who is one with loss,      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Loss is also pleased to have him. |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | If you do not trust enough, then  |
|                                   | you will not have                 |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       anyone’s trust.             |
