Chapter Twenty Four

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 企 者 不 立                       | He who stands on tiptoe does not  |
|                                   | really stand.                     |
| 跨 者 不 行                       |                                   |
|                                   | He who stands astride can not     |
| 自 見 者 不 明                    | travel.                           |
|                                   |                                   |
| 自 是 者 不 彰 •                  | He who displays himself does not  |
|                                   | have insight.                     |
| 自 伐 者 無 功                    |                                   |
|                                   | He who considers himself correct  |
| 自 矜 者 不 長                    | does not distinguish              |
|                                   |                                   |
| 其 在 道 也(•)                    |       himself.                    |
|                                   |                                   |
| 曰 餘 食 贅 行 •                  | He who boasts about himself is    |
|                                   | without merit.                    |
| 物 或 惡 之                       |                                   |
|                                   | He who brags about himself does   |
| (•)故 有 道 者 不 處 •            | not endure.                       |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | He who lives in Dao –             |
|                                   | Calls these leftover food and     |
|                                   | unnecessary behavior.             |
|                                   | Creatures detest them, no matter  |
|                                   | what.                             |
|                                   | Therefore : he who possesses Dao  |
|                                   | does not live by them.            |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| He who stands on tiptoe does not  | Notes                             |
| [really] stand.                   |                                   |
| He who stands astride can not     | A : presumably, the inedible      |
| travel.                           | scraps (not something good, as in |
|                                   | “leftover turkey”)                |
| ♦He who displays himself does not |                                   |
| have insight.                     | B : there is some debate over the |
|                                   | last symbol in this line – both   |
|                                   | FY and HSG use this symbol        |
|          [shows] [wise,sight]     | (making it a majority), and some  |
|                                   | WB versions also use it; other WB |
| ♦He who considers himself correct | versions use 处, thus reading     |
| does not distinguish              |                                   |
|                                   |             he who possesses Dao  |
|       himself.                    | does not dwell with them          |
|          [manifest,displayàstand  |                                   |
| out]                              |                                   |
