Chapter Twenty Seven

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 善 行 無 轍 迹                    | A good traveler is without wagon  |
|                                   | track or footprint.               |
| 善 言 無 瑕 謫                    |                                   |
|                                   | A good speaker is without flaw or |
| 善 數 不 用 籌 策                 | disgrace.                         |
|                                   |                                   |
| 善 閉 無 關 楗 而 不 可 開 •      | A good accountant does not use    |
|                                   | counting tokens.                  |
| 善 結 無 纆 約 而 不 可 解        |                                   |
| •                                 | A good barrier is without bar or  |
|                                   | lock, yet can not be              |
| 是 以 聖 人                       |                                   |
|                                   |       opened.                     |
| 常 善 救 人                       |                                   |
|                                   | A good binding is without cord or |
| 故 無 棄 人                       | restraint, yet can not be         |
|                                   |                                   |
| 常 善 救 物                       |       loosened.                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 故 無 棄 物 •                     |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 是 謂 襲 明                       | Thus the sage :                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| (•)故 善 人 者 不 善 人 之 師     | Is always good at helping people, |
|                                   |                                   |
| 不 善 人 者 善 人 之 資 •         | Therefore he does not abandon     |
|                                   | people.                           |
| 不 貴 其 師                       |                                   |
|                                   | Is always good at helping         |
| 不 愛 其 資                       | creatures,                        |
|                                   |                                   |
| 雖 智 大 迷                       | Therefore he does not abandon     |
|                                   | creatures.                        |
| 是 謂 要 妙                       |                                   |
|                                   | This is called following your     |
|                                   | insight.                          |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Therefore : he who is a virtuous  |
|                                   | person is the teacher of he       |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       who is not a virtuous       |
|                                   | person.                           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | He who is not a virtuous person   |
|                                   | is the resource of he who         |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       is a virtuous               |
|                                   | person.                           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | If the latter does not value his  |
|                                   | teacher,                          |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Or the former does not love his   |
|                                   | resource,                         |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Even if there is wisdom, there    |
|                                   | will be great confusion.          |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | This is called the essential      |
|                                   | subtle mystery.                   |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
