Chapter Forty Nine

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 聖 人 無 常 心                    | The sage does not have a constant |
|                                   | heart/mind,                       |
| 以 百 姓 心 為 心                 |                                   |
|                                   | Thus the 100 families’            |
| 善 者 吾 善 之                    | heart/minds become his            |
|                                   | heart/mind.                       |
| 不 善 者 吾 亦 善 之              |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 德 善 •                           |                                   |
|                                   | He who is virtuous, I am virtuous |
| 信 者 吾 信 之                    | to him.                           |
|                                   |                                   |
| 不 信 者 吾 亦 信 之              | He who is not virtuous, I am also |
|                                   | virtuous to him.                  |
| 德 信 •                           |                                   |
|                                   | Because De is virtue.             |
| 聖 人 在 天 下 歙 歙              |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| [焉] 為 天 下 渾 其 心            |                                   |
|                                   | He who is honest, I am honest     |
| 百 姓 皆 注 其 耳 目              | with him.                         |
|                                   |                                   |
| 聖 人 皆 孩 之                    | He who is not honest, I am also   |
|                                   | honest with him.                  |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Because De is honesty.            |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | The sage lives in the world,      |
|                                   | gathering it all in.              |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | And so he serves the world,       |
|                                   | merging with their                |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       heart/minds.                |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | The 100 families all pay          |
|                                   | attention to their ears and eyes, |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | And the sage treats them all like |
|                                   | his children.                     |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| The sage² does not have a         | Notes                             |
| constant heart/mind,              |                                   |
|                                   | A : compare to #50, which refers  |
| ♦Thus the 100 families’           | to one who “takes in life”;       |
| heart/minds become his            | “gathering” is used for           |
|                                   | consistency with #36; the         |
|       heart/mind.                 | repeated symbol implies “very”,   |
|                                   | hence completeness                |
| ♦He who is virtuous, I am         |                                   |
| virtuous to him.                  | B : this line can be translated   |
|                                   | in many ways, mainly due to the   |
| ♦He who is not virtuous, I am     | fact that the symbol for “merges” |
| also virtuous to him.             | can also mean “muddled” or        |
|                                   | “whole”; also 其 (his/their)      |
| ♦Because De is virtue.            | could be referring to the sage or |
|                                   | to the 100 families; the choices  |
| ♦He who is honest*, I am honest*  | made here are consistent with the |
| with him.                         | first two lines of the chapter    |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦He who is not honest*, I am also | C : compare to #12, where the     |
| honest* with him.                 | sage does not act on what he sees |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦Because De is honesty*.          | D : adding “his” turns this line  |
|                                   | from something deragatory         |
| ♦The sage² lives in the world²,   | (“treats them all like children”, |
| gathering it all in^(2A).         | which seems out of character)     |
|                                   | into something that matches #42,  |
|                                   | where the sage becomes an “elder  |
|        [inhale inhale]            | teacher” (literally, godfather)   |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦And so he serves the world²,     |                                   |
| merging with their                |                                   |
|                                   | Cross-references                  |
|       heart/minds.^(B)            |                                   |
|                                   | 100 families : #5, #17            |
| ♦The 100 families all pay         |                                   |
| attention to their ears and       | one who is not virtuous : #27,    |
| eyes^(C),                         | #62, #81                          |
|                                   |                                   |
| ♦And the sage² treats them all    | serve the world : #13, #39        |
