Chapter Fifty Nine

+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| 治 人 事 天                       | When governing people or doing    |
|                                   | heaven’s duties,                  |
| 莫 若 嗇                          |                                   |
|                                   | It is better to be sparing.       |
| (•)夫 唯 嗇                       |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 是 謂 早 服                       |                                   |
|                                   | Now : only when you can be        |
| 早 服 謂 之 重 積 德              | sparing,                          |
|                                   |                                   |
| 重 積 德                          | This is called early acceptance.  |
|                                   |                                   |
| 則 無 不 克 •                     | Early acceptance is called        |
|                                   | doubling your accumulation of     |
| 無 不 克                          |                                   |
|                                   |       De.                         |
| 則 莫 知 其 極                    |                                   |
|                                   | With a double accumulation of De, |
| 莫 知 其 極                       |                                   |
|                                   | Then everything can be overcome.  |
| 可 以 有 國                       |                                   |
|                                   | When everything can be overcome,  |
| 有 國 之 母                       |                                   |
|                                   | Then no one knows your limits.    |
| 可 以 長 久                       |                                   |
|                                   | When no one knows your limits,    |
| 是 謂 深 根 固 柢                 |                                   |
|                                   | You can possess the nation.       |
| 長 生 久 視 之 道 • •             |                                   |
|                                   | Possessing the mother of the      |
|                                   | nation,                           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | You can forever endure.           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | This is called having a deep      |
|                                   | source and a firm foundation,     |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | The Way of long life and enduring |
|                                   | sight.                            |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| ♦When governing people or doing   | Notes                             |
| heaven’s duties,                  |                                   |
|                                   | A : this is the most literal      |
| ♦It is better² to be sparing.     | translation; GUO has              |
|                                   |                                   |
|        [stingy,thrifty]           |             Thus you are prepared |
|                                   | in advance                        |
| Now : only when you can be        | [early]                           |
| sparing,                          |                                   |
| [stingy,thrifty]                  | B : literally “your extremes”,    |
|                                   | presumably in the sense of “to    |
| This is called early              | what extremes you will go” or     |
| acceptance^(A).          [be      | “how far will you go”; compare to |
| convinced,serve]                  | #58                               |
|                                   |                                   |
