| 無 執 故 無 失 •                  | A journey of a thousand miles     |
|                                   | begins from under the feet.       |
| 民 之 從 事 常 於 幾 成 而 敗 之  |                                   |
| •                                 |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 慎 終 如 始                       | He who acts, ruins it.            |
|                                   |                                   |
| 則 無 敗 事 •                     | He who grasps, loses it.          |
|                                   |                                   |
| 是 以 聖 人                       |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 欲 不 欲                          | Thus the sage :                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 不 貴 難 得 之 貨                 | Does not act, therefore he does   |
|                                   | not ruin.                         |
| 學 不 學 •                        |                                   |
|                                   | Does not grasp, therefore he does |
| 復 眾 人 之 所 過 •               | not lose.                         |
|                                   |                                   |
| 以 輔 萬 物 之 自 然              |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
