|  天 下 皆 謂 我 __ 大             | In the world, all say I am great, |
|                                   |                                   |
| 似 不 肖                          | But do not seem to be like        |
|                                   | everyone else.                    |
| (•)夫 唯 (不 肖) 故 [能] (大)  •  |                                   |
|                                   | Now : only because I am not like  |
| 若 肖 •                           | everyone else, therefore I        |
|                                   |                                   |
| 久 矣 其 細 也(•)                 |       can be great.               |
|                                   |                                   |
| (•)夫 我 有 三 寶                 | If I was like everyone else,      |
|                                   |                                   |
| 持 而 保 之 •                     | Long ago! I would have become     |
|                                   | insignificant, indeed!            |
| 一 曰 慈 •                        |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 二 曰 儉                          |                                   |
|                                   | Now : I possess three treasures – |
| 三 曰 不 敢 為 天 下 先           |                                   |
|                                   | Hold and maintain them.           |
| 慈 故 能 勇                       |                                   |
|                                   | The first is called compassion,   |
| 儉 故 能 廣                       |                                   |
|                                   | The second is called economy,     |
| 不 敢 為 天 下 先                 |                                   |
|                                   | The third is called not daring to |
| (•)故 能 成 器 長 •               | act first in the world.           |
|                                   |                                   |
| 今 舍 慈 且 勇 •                  |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
| 舍 儉 且 廣                       | With compassion, you can          |
|                                   | therefore be brave.               |
| 舍 後 且 先                       |                                   |
|                                   | With economy, you can therefore   |
| 死 矣(•)                          | expand.                           |
|                                   |                                   |
| (•)夫 慈 以 戰 則 勝              | By not daring to act first in the |
|                                   | world,                            |
| 以 守 則 固                       |                                   |
|                                   | Therefore you can achieve the     |
| 天 將 救 之                       | capacity for leadership.          |
|                                   |                                   |
| 以 慈 衛 之                       |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | At present, people abandon        |
|                                   | compassion but also try to be     |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       brave,                      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Abandon economy but also try to   |
|                                   | expand,                           |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Abandon being behind but also try |
|                                   | to be first –                     |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | This is death!                    |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Now : when compassion is used in  |
|                                   | war, the consequence              |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   |       is victory.                 |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | When it is used for protection,   |
|                                   | the consequence is strength.      |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | When heaven would help you,       |
|                                   |                                   |
|                                   | Using compassion it protects you. |
+-----------------------------------+-----------------------------------+
| In the world², all say I am       | Notes                             |
| great,^(A)                        |                                   |
